### Priority 3 — EventChainDef Framework

---

#### [NEW] [event_chain.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/event_chain.rs)

`EventChainDef` is the **universal event container** — legislation, crises, diplomacy, minigames all use this format:

```rust
pub struct EventChainDef {
    pub id: String,
    pub name: String,
    pub description: String,
    pub ideological_coordinate: (f64, f64),
    pub base_aut_cost: f64,
    pub phases: Vec<EventPhase>,
}

pub struct EventPhase {
    pub name: String,
    pub description: String,
    pub player_choices: Vec<EventChoice>,
}

pub struct EventChoice {
    pub label: String,
    pub metric_deltas: Vec<(String, f64)>,
    pub pass_chance_modifier: f64,
    pub ideological_shift: Option<(f64, f64)>,
}

pub enum EventOutcome {
    Success(Vec<(String, f64)>),
    Failure(Vec<(String, f64)>),
    Compromised(Vec<(String, f64)>),  // "Pork-Barrel" — guaranteed pass with cost
}
```

#### [MODIFY] [state.rs](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs)

Add `active_events: Vec<EventChainDef>` and `event_log: Vec<String>` to [State](file:///c:/Users/zephy/Documents/Brinkmanship/brinkmanship_engine/src/state.rs#152-172).

